    <description>
        <div>
            <p>In the Economic Cooperation Act of 1948 (Apr 3, 1948; 62 Stat. 138), Congress
                established the Economic Cooperation Administration to administer the European
                Recovery Program (Marshall Plan). The Administrator was appointed by the President
                with the advice and consent of the Senate. The Mutual Security Act of Oct 10, 1951
                (65 Stat. 378) abolished the ECA and transferred its functions to the Mutual
                Security Agency, effective Dec 30, 1951.</p>
        </div>
    </description>
